using boost

place the boost directory into your root folder. This makes it easier to invoke the libraries in your command line

GENERIC COMPILE EXAMPLE:
g++ -I path/to/boost_1_57_0 example.cpp -o example

HOW I COMPILED:
g++ -I/boost_1_57_0 *.cpp -o server2

yeah i used wildcard.

reference:
http://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_57_0/more/getting_started/unix-variants.html#build-a-simple-program-using-boost
